introduction: The villain of a historical epic struggles with the fact that this epic also happens to be a musical

vocabulary.definition: a term used in the context of the text, could be a proper noun or a specific name
vocabulary.example: Legateaux was a mysterious character in the play.

vocabulary.definition: a building or group of buildings used to house soldiers
vocabulary.example: The soldiers gathered in the barracks before heading out for training.

vocabulary.definition: to break the continuity of something by causing a disturbance or stopping an action
vocabulary.example: Please do not interrupt me while I am speaking.

vocabulary.definition: a female child in relation to her parents
vocabulary.example: She was excited to see her daughter after a long trip.

vocabulary.definition: to continue to live or exist, especially in difficult circumstances
vocabulary.example: The hiker had to use all his survival skills to make it through the wilderness.

vocabulary.definition: relating to or characteristic of an orchestra
vocabulary.example: The orchestral performance at the concert was breathtaking.
